                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/7733: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-10-09T14:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 9, 1926—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>224. Press reports dreadful suffering civilian population in Wuchang. You are
                    instructed to correspond with Lockhart in the endeavor to ascertain whether we
                    can be of assistance.</p>
                <p>Your 465, October 9, 3 p.m., just received. Should situation of civilian
                    population in Wuchang become such as to seem to justify it, it is suggested that
                    consular body in Hankow endeavor to arrange armistice, during which some means
                    of relief might be devised. Red Cross would be disposed to assist in case of
                    necessity. Wire your recommendation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
